<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-how-to-make-the-best-peach-cobbler">How to Make the Best Peach Cobbler</h2>



<p><strong>You&rsquo;ll find the full recipe below.</strong> Here&rsquo;s a brief preview of the process and why it works so well: </p>



<ol class="wp-block-list">
<li>Mix together the filling ingredients directly in your baking dish to avoid dirtying another dish. Bake the filling for about 20 minutes while you prepare the topping. With this two-step baking process, you&rsquo;ll achieve a bubbly, condensed peach filling with a perfectly golden topping. If you try to bake it all together at once, the topping will turn too golden before the filling is done (I know because I tried). </li>



<li>The topping comes together in a few simple steps. You&rsquo;ll want to combine the sugar and lemon zest in a small bowl, and use your fingers to rub the zest into the sugar (this takes about 20 seconds and maximizes the lemon flavor). We&rsquo;ll grate cold butter into the flour for a biscuit-like texture. Lastly, we&rsquo;ll whisk together an egg with some yogurt before stirring into the flour for even dispersion. </li>



<li>Dollop big spoonfuls of topping over the bubbling filling, and bake until the topping is lightly golden. Serve your cobbler with vanilla ice cream or <a href="https://cookieandkate.com/best-whipped-cream-recipe/">whipped cream</a>. Leftovers are fantastic the next day with Greek yogurt for breakfast!</li>
</ol>



