<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-more-peach-treats">More Peach Treats</h2>



<p>Make the most of your ripe summer <a href="https://cookieandkate.com/tag/peaches/">peaches</a> with these sweet peachy treats: </p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><a href="https://cookieandkate.com/gluten-free-peach-pancakes/">Caramelized Peach and Oat Pancakes</a></li>



<li><a href="https://cookieandkate.com/peach-honey-popsicles-recipe/">Creamy Peach &amp; Honey Popsicles</a></li>



<li><a href="https://cookieandkate.com/simple-fruit-compote-recipe/">Easy Fruit Compote</a></li>



<li><a href="https://cookieandkate.com/fresh-bellini-recipe/">Fresh Bellini Cocktail</a></li>



<li><a href="https://cookieandkate.com/gluten-free-peach-crisp-recipe/">Peach Crisp (Gluten-Free)</a></li>
</ul>



<p><strong>This is my first cobbler recipe on the blog, and it certainly won&rsquo;t be my last.</strong> I&rsquo;ve long declared myself a <a href="https://cookieandkate.com/category/food-recipes/dessert/crisps/">crisp</a> gal, but now that I&rsquo;ve cracked the code to perfect cobblers, I can&rsquo;t quit trying every fruity flavor. Why not?  </p>



<p><strong>Please let me know how your cobbler turns out in the comments!</strong> I love hearing from you. </p>



