	<li id="comment-904560" class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1 parent">
		<article id="div-comment-904560" class="comment-body">
			<footer class="comment-meta">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
										<b class="fn">Mary</b>				</div><!-- .comment-author -->

				<div class="comment-metadata">
					<time datetime="2025-08-05T19:23:36-05:00">August 5, 2025 at 7:23 PM</time>				</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

							</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>What would you recommend for substitutes to make it dairy free?</p>
			</div><!-- .comment-content -->

			<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-904560" data-commentid="904560" data-postid="46896" data-belowelement="div-comment-904560" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Mary" aria-label="Reply to Mary">Reply</a></div>		</article><!-- .comment-body -->
	<ol class="children">
	<li id="comment-905470" class="comment byuser comment-author-admin bypostauthor even depth-2 staff">
		<article id="div-comment-905470" class="comment-body">
			<footer class="comment-meta">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
										<b class="fn">Kathryne Taylor</b>				</div><!-- .comment-author -->

				<div class="comment-metadata">
					<time datetime="2025-08-12T13:50:11-05:00">August 12, 2025 at 1:50 PM</time>				</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

							</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Hi Mary, I would use your preferred non-dairy butter (if you can&#8217;t grate it, you can lightly melt it) and non-dairy yogurt (ideally one that is plain and thick).</p>
			</div><!-- .comment-content -->

			<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-905470" data-commentid="905470" data-postid="46896" data-belowelement="div-comment-905470" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Kathryne Taylor" aria-label="Reply to Kathryne Taylor">Reply</a></div>		</article><!-- .comment-body -->
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ol><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li id="comment-904565" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 parent">
		<article id="div-comment-904565" class="comment-body">
			<footer class="comment-meta">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
										<b class="fn">Mooinca</b>				</div><!-- .comment-author -->

				<div class="comment-metadata">
					<time datetime="2025-08-05T20:24:59-05:00">August 5, 2025 at 8:24 PM</time>				</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

							</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>What could I replace the egg with? Looks so yummy. I LOVE Almond Flour!</p>
<p class="tasty-recipes-ratings"><span class="tasty-recipes-rating tasty-recipes-rating-solid" data-tr-clip="100" data-rating="1"><svg class="tasty-recipes-svg" width="18" height="17"><use href="#wpt-star-full"></use></svg></span><span class="tasty-recipes-rating tasty-recipes-rating-solid" data-tr-clip="100" data-rating="2"><svg class="tasty-recipes-svg" width="18" height="17"><use href="#wpt-star-full"></use></svg></span><span class="tasty-recipes-rating tasty-recipes-rating-solid" data-tr-clip="100" data-rating="3"><svg class="tasty-recipes-svg" width="18" height="17"><use href="#wpt-star-full"></use></svg></span><span class="tasty-recipes-rating tasty-recipes-rating-solid" data-tr-clip="100" data-rating="4"><svg class="tasty-recipes-svg" width="18" height="17"><use href="#wpt-star-full"></use></svg></span><span class="tasty-recipes-rating tasty-recipes-rating-solid" data-tr-clip="100" data-rating="5"><svg class="tasty-recipes-svg" width="18" height="17"><use href="#wpt-star-full"></use></svg></span></p>
			</div><!-- .comment-content -->

			<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-904565" data-commentid="904565" data-postid="46896" data-belowelement="div-comment-904565" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Mooinca" aria-label="Reply to Mooinca">Reply</a></div>		</article><!-- .comment-body -->
	<ol class="children">
	<li id="comment-905465" class="comment byuser comment-author-admin bypostauthor even depth-2 staff">
		<article id="div-comment-905465" class="comment-body">
			<footer class="comment-meta">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
										<b class="fn">Kathryne Taylor</b>				</div><!-- .comment-author -->

				<div class="comment-metadata">
					<time datetime="2025-08-12T13:44:57-05:00">August 12, 2025 at 1:44 PM</time>				</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

							</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Hi there! Unfortunately, I&#8217;ve not had luck with flax eggs in almond flour recipes. There&#8217;s a good chance you could omit the egg altogether—the topping will be more crumbly, but that&#8217;s ok on a cobbler!</p>
			</div><!-- .comment-content -->

			<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-905465" data-commentid="905465" data-postid="46896" data-belowelement="div-comment-905465" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Kathryne Taylor" aria-label="Reply to Kathryne Taylor">Reply</a></div>		</article><!-- .comment-body -->
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ol><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li id="comment-904566" class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1 parent">
		<article id="div-comment-904566" class="comment-body">
			<footer class="comment-meta">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
										<b class="fn">Elizabeth L Richards</b>				</div><!-- .comment-author -->

				<div class="comment-metadata">
					<time datetime="2025-08-05T20:25:02-05:00">August 5, 2025 at 8:25 PM</time>				</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

							</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>we are starting to see peach season passing. The last peaches I got weren’t great. Have you tried this with frozen peaches?</p>
			</div><!-- .comment-content -->

			<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-904566" data-commentid="904566" data-postid="46896" data-belowelement="div-comment-904566" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Elizabeth L Richards" aria-label="Reply to Elizabeth L Richards">Reply</a></div>		</article><!-- .comment-body -->
	<ol class="children">
	<li id="comment-905471" class="comment byuser comment-author-admin bypostauthor even depth-2 staff">
		<article id="div-comment-905471" class="comment-body">
			<footer class="comment-meta">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
										<b class="fn">Kathryne Taylor</b>				</div><!-- .comment-author -->

				<div class="comment-metadata">
					<time datetime="2025-08-12T13:51:02-05:00">August 12, 2025 at 1:51 PM</time>				</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

							</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Hi Elizabeth, I&#8217;ve not tried the recipe with frozen peaches. I generally don&#8217;t find store-bought frozen peaches to be as tasty as ripe summer peaches, but if you have a good source, it would be worth a try! I would let the peaches defrost first, drain off excess water, then bake as directed. The filling might need a few extra minutes in the oven since the peaches are starting out cold.</p>
			</div><!-- .comment-content -->

			<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-905471" data-commentid="905471" data-postid="46896" data-belowelement="div-comment-905471" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Kathryne Taylor" aria-label="Reply to Kathryne Taylor">Reply</a></div>		</article><!-- .comment-body -->
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ol><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li id="comment-904682" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 parent">
		<article id="div-comment-904682" class="comment-body">
			<footer class="comment-meta">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
										<b class="fn">Laurey Fitzgerald</b>				</div><!-- .comment-author -->

				<div class="comment-metadata">
					<time datetime="2025-08-06T20:11:34-05:00">August 6, 2025 at 8:11 PM</time>				</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

							</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Can this be made with non-fat Greek yogurt? I always have that on hand. Thanks, it sounds delicious! I realize it won’t be as creamy.</p>
			</div><!-- .comment-content -->

			<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-904682" data-commentid="904682" data-postid="46896" data-belowelement="div-comment-904682" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Laurey Fitzgerald" aria-label="Reply to Laurey Fitzgerald">Reply</a></div>		</article><!-- .comment-body -->
	<ol class="children">
	<li id="comment-905464" class="comment byuser comment-author-admin bypostauthor even depth-2 staff">
		<article id="div-comment-905464" class="comment-body">
			<footer class="comment-meta">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
										<b class="fn">Kathryne Taylor</b>				</div><!-- .comment-author -->

				<div class="comment-metadata">
					<time datetime="2025-08-12T13:44:04-05:00">August 12, 2025 at 1:44 PM</time>				</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

							</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Sure, that should work well enough!</p>
			</div><!-- .comment-content -->

			<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-905464" data-commentid="905464" data-postid="46896" data-belowelement="div-comment-905464" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Kathryne Taylor" aria-label="Reply to Kathryne Taylor">Reply</a></div>		</article><!-- .comment-body -->
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ol><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li id="comment-904703" class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1 parent">
		<article id="div-comment-904703" class="comment-body">
			<footer class="comment-meta">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
										<b class="fn">SJB</b>				</div><!-- .comment-author -->

				<div class="comment-metadata">
					<time datetime="2025-08-07T00:26:41-05:00">August 7, 2025 at 12:26 AM</time>				</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

							</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>It was every bit as delicious as I hoped it would be!</p>
<p class="tasty-recipes-ratings"><span class="tasty-recipes-rating tasty-recipes-rating-solid" data-tr-clip="100" data-rating="1"><svg class="tasty-recipes-svg" width="18" height="17"><use href="#wpt-star-full"></use></svg></span><span class="tasty-recipes-rating tasty-recipes-rating-solid" data-tr-clip="100" data-rating="2"><svg class="tasty-recipes-svg" width="18" height="17"><use href="#wpt-star-full"></use></svg></span><span class="tasty-recipes-rating tasty-recipes-rating-solid" data-tr-clip="100" data-rating="3"><svg class="tasty-recipes-svg" width="18" height="17"><use href="#wpt-star-full"></use></svg></span><span class="tasty-recipes-rating tasty-recipes-rating-solid" data-tr-clip="100" data-rating="4"><svg class="tasty-recipes-svg" width="18" height="17"><use href="#wpt-star-full"></use></svg></span><span class="tasty-recipes-rating tasty-recipes-rating-solid" data-tr-clip="100" data-rating="5"><svg class="tasty-recipes-svg" width="18" height="17"><use href="#wpt-star-full"></use></svg></span></p>
			</div><!-- .comment-content -->

			<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-904703" data-commentid="904703" data-postid="46896" data-belowelement="div-comment-904703" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to SJB" aria-label="Reply to SJB">Reply</a></div>		</article><!-- .comment-body -->
	<ol class="children">
	<li id="comment-905463" class="comment byuser comment-author-admin bypostauthor even depth-2 staff">
		<article id="div-comment-905463" class="comment-body">
			<footer class="comment-meta">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
										<b class="fn">Kathryne Taylor</b>				</div><!-- .comment-author -->

				<div class="comment-metadata">
					<time datetime="2025-08-12T13:43:51-05:00">August 12, 2025 at 1:43 PM</time>				</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

							</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Fantastic! Thank you for letting me know!</p>
			</div><!-- .comment-content -->

			<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-905463" data-commentid="905463" data-postid="46896" data-belowelement="div-comment-905463" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Kathryne Taylor" aria-label="Reply to Kathryne Taylor">Reply</a></div>		</article><!-- .comment-body -->
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ol><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li id="comment-904738" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 parent">
		<article id="div-comment-904738" class="comment-body">
			<footer class="comment-meta">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
										<b class="fn">Sally Allen-Smith</b>				</div><!-- .comment-author -->

				<div class="comment-metadata">
					<time datetime="2025-08-07T08:47:54-05:00">August 7, 2025 at 8:47 AM</time>				</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

							</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Can&#8217;t wait to find good peaches to try this incredible recipe.  For now, I want to tell you how grateful to you I am for your gluten free recipes.  I really appreciate you.  When I was diagnosed with gluten enteropathy (newly named &#8220;celiac&#8221;) 40 years ago. it was impossible to dine out or find recipes that didn&#8217;t require drastic revisions, so please know that your recipes bring joy to my life and excellent food to my table. Thank you so much.</p>
			</div><!-- .comment-content -->

			<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-904738" data-commentid="904738" data-postid="46896" data-belowelement="div-comment-904738" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Sally Allen-Smith" aria-label="Reply to Sally Allen-Smith">Reply</a></div>		</article><!-- .comment-body -->
	<ol class="children">
	<li id="comment-905469" class="comment byuser comment-author-admin bypostauthor even depth-2 staff">
		<article id="div-comment-905469" class="comment-body">
			<footer class="comment-meta">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
										<b class="fn">Kathryne Taylor</b>				</div><!-- .comment-author -->

				<div class="comment-metadata">
					<time datetime="2025-08-12T13:49:09-05:00">August 12, 2025 at 1:49 PM</time>				</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

							</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Sally, thank you for your note! I really appreciate it. I&#8217;ve had fun playing with almond flour lately—it has so many great qualities! I&#8217;m not gluten free but I do have some blood sugar issues, so almond flour works better for me, too.</p>
			</div><!-- .comment-content -->

			<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-905469" data-commentid="905469" data-postid="46896" data-belowelement="div-comment-905469" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Kathryne Taylor" aria-label="Reply to Kathryne Taylor">Reply</a></div>		</article><!-- .comment-body -->
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ol><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li id="comment-905052" class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1 parent">
		<article id="div-comment-905052" class="comment-body">
			<footer class="comment-meta">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
										<b class="fn">Linda</b>				</div><!-- .comment-author -->

				<div class="comment-metadata">
					<time datetime="2025-08-09T12:15:00-05:00">August 9, 2025 at 12:15 PM</time>				</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

							</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Hiya, i had recently picked 10 lbs of gorgeous peaches that I froze for later use. Can this be made with frozen peaches?</p>
			</div><!-- .comment-content -->

			<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-905052" data-commentid="905052" data-postid="46896" data-belowelement="div-comment-905052" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Linda" aria-label="Reply to Linda">Reply</a></div>		</article><!-- .comment-body -->
	<ol class="children">
	<li id="comment-905468" class="comment byuser comment-author-admin bypostauthor even depth-2 staff">
		<article id="div-comment-905468" class="comment-body">
			<footer class="comment-meta">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
										<b class="fn">Kathryne Taylor</b>				</div><!-- .comment-author -->

				<div class="comment-metadata">
					<time datetime="2025-08-12T13:48:25-05:00">August 12, 2025 at 1:48 PM</time>				</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

							</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Hi Linda! I haven&#8217;t tried, but I bet it would turn out lovely since your peaches were so good to begin with. I would let the peaches defrost first, drain off excess water, then bake as directed. The filling might need a few extra minutes in the oven since the peaches are starting out cold.</p>
			</div><!-- .comment-content -->

			<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-905468" data-commentid="905468" data-postid="46896" data-belowelement="div-comment-905468" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Kathryne Taylor" aria-label="Reply to Kathryne Taylor">Reply</a></div>		</article><!-- .comment-body -->
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ol><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li id="comment-905100" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 parent">
		<article id="div-comment-905100" class="comment-body">
			<footer class="comment-meta">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
										<b class="fn">Paula</b>				</div><!-- .comment-author -->

				<div class="comment-metadata">
					<time datetime="2025-08-09T19:54:37-05:00">August 9, 2025 at 7:54 PM</time>				</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

							</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>My peach cobbler did not turn out so well. I have so much left over topping &#8211; at least half of the bowl. The little dollops look like madelines on top of the peaches. No idea what I didn&#8217;t do correctly. My dry mixture never formed a cohesive dough once the wet ingredients were added. Shaving the butter with a box cutter seems unnecessary. I did it for 4 tbls but used butter at table top temperature for the last tbls. It mixed in fine. I like your recipes and have tried many with success &#8212; just not this one.</p>
<p class="tasty-recipes-ratings"><span class="tasty-recipes-rating tasty-recipes-rating-solid" data-tr-clip="100" data-rating="1"><svg class="tasty-recipes-svg" width="18" height="17"><use href="#wpt-star-full"></use></svg></span><span class="tasty-recipes-rating tasty-recipes-rating-solid" data-tr-clip="100" data-rating="2"><svg class="tasty-recipes-svg" width="18" height="17"><use href="#wpt-star-full"></use></svg></span><span class="tasty-recipes-rating tasty-recipes-rating-solid" data-tr-clip="100" data-rating="3"><svg class="tasty-recipes-svg" width="18" height="17"><use href="#wpt-star-full"></use></svg></span><span class="tasty-recipes-rating tasty-recipes-rating-solid" data-tr-clip="0" data-rating="4"><svg class="tasty-recipes-svg" width="18" height="17"><use href="#wpt-star-full"></use></svg></span><span class="tasty-recipes-rating tasty-recipes-rating-solid" data-tr-clip="0" data-rating="5"><svg class="tasty-recipes-svg" width="18" height="17"><use href="#wpt-star-full"></use></svg></span></p>
			</div><!-- .comment-content -->

			<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-905100" data-commentid="905100" data-postid="46896" data-belowelement="div-comment-905100" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Paula" aria-label="Reply to Paula">Reply</a></div>		</article><!-- .comment-body -->
	<ol class="children">
	<li id="comment-905467" class="comment byuser comment-author-admin bypostauthor even depth-2 parent staff">
		<article id="div-comment-905467" class="comment-body">
			<footer class="comment-meta">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
										<b class="fn">Kathryne Taylor</b>				</div><!-- .comment-author -->

				<div class="comment-metadata">
					<time datetime="2025-08-12T13:47:15-05:00">August 12, 2025 at 1:47 PM</time>				</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

							</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Hi Paula, I&#8217;m sorry to hear that! The cobbler is designed for this amount of topping—you can see in the photos and videos that I used decently large scoops of topping to cover it. For this almond flour-based recipe, I found it important to really mix in the butter, more than I would with a gluten-based flour. It sounds like yours didn&#8217;t get stirred enough. Just melted butter works, too, but the texture is not quite as nice in the end result. I&#8217;d love to hear from you on the recipes that have turned out well.</p>
			</div><!-- .comment-content -->

			<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-905467" data-commentid="905467" data-postid="46896" data-belowelement="div-comment-905467" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Kathryne Taylor" aria-label="Reply to Kathryne Taylor">Reply</a></div>		</article><!-- .comment-body -->
	<ol class="children">
	<li id="comment-905605" class="comment odd alt depth-3">
		<article id="div-comment-905605" class="comment-body">
			<footer class="comment-meta">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
										<b class="fn">Paula</b>				</div><!-- .comment-author -->

				<div class="comment-metadata">
					<time datetime="2025-08-13T16:41:35-05:00">August 13, 2025 at 4:41 PM</time>				</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

							</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Thank you Katherine for your reply and your suggestions for what I might have done differently. Had I watched the video I might have had a clearer understanding of how you meant the &#8220;dollops&#8221; to be on the top. In any event, here is the list of recipes we have tried and loved: Butternut Squash Mac &amp; Cheese; Roasted Veggie enchilada casserole; That Peanut Dressing; Hasselback potatoes, Roasted Brussel Sprouts and Crispy Tofu Honey Sesame Glaze.<br />
Onward to the next creation!!</p>
			</div><!-- .comment-content -->

			<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-905605" data-commentid="905605" data-postid="46896" data-belowelement="div-comment-905605" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Paula" aria-label="Reply to Paula">Reply</a></div>		</article><!-- .comment-body -->
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ol><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ol><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li id="comment-905160" class="comment even thread-even depth-1 parent">
		<article id="div-comment-905160" class="comment-body">
			<footer class="comment-meta">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
										<b class="fn">Denise</b>				</div><!-- .comment-author -->

				<div class="comment-metadata">
					<time datetime="2025-08-10T07:21:03-05:00">August 10, 2025 at 7:21 AM</time>				</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

							</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Utterly delicious, thanks for another great recipe!</p>
<p class="tasty-recipes-ratings"><span class="tasty-recipes-rating tasty-recipes-rating-solid" data-tr-clip="100" data-rating="1"><svg class="tasty-recipes-svg" width="18" height="17"><use href="#wpt-star-full"></use></svg></span><span class="tasty-recipes-rating tasty-recipes-rating-solid" data-tr-clip="100" data-rating="2"><svg class="tasty-recipes-svg" width="18" height="17"><use href="#wpt-star-full"></use></svg></span><span class="tasty-recipes-rating tasty-recipes-rating-solid" data-tr-clip="100" data-rating="3"><svg class="tasty-recipes-svg" width="18" height="17"><use href="#wpt-star-full"></use></svg></span><span class="tasty-recipes-rating tasty-recipes-rating-solid" data-tr-clip="100" data-rating="4"><svg class="tasty-recipes-svg" width="18" height="17"><use href="#wpt-star-full"></use></svg></span><span class="tasty-recipes-rating tasty-recipes-rating-solid" data-tr-clip="100" data-rating="5"><svg class="tasty-recipes-svg" width="18" height="17"><use href="#wpt-star-full"></use></svg></span></p>
			</div><!-- .comment-content -->

			<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-905160" data-commentid="905160" data-postid="46896" data-belowelement="div-comment-905160" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Denise" aria-label="Reply to Denise">Reply</a></div>		</article><!-- .comment-body -->
	<ol class="children">
	<li id="comment-905461" class="comment byuser comment-author-admin bypostauthor odd alt depth-2 staff">
		<article id="div-comment-905461" class="comment-body">
			<footer class="comment-meta">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
										<b class="fn">Kathryne Taylor</b>				</div><!-- .comment-author -->

				<div class="comment-metadata">
					<time datetime="2025-08-12T13:42:16-05:00">August 12, 2025 at 1:42 PM</time>				</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

							</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Thank you, Denise!</p>
			</div><!-- .comment-content -->

			<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-905461" data-commentid="905461" data-postid="46896" data-belowelement="div-comment-905461" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Kathryne Taylor" aria-label="Reply to Kathryne Taylor">Reply</a></div>		</article><!-- .comment-body -->
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ol><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li id="comment-905345" class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 parent">
		<article id="div-comment-905345" class="comment-body">
			<footer class="comment-meta">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
										<b class="fn">Nancy A Rini</b>				</div><!-- .comment-author -->

				<div class="comment-metadata">
					<time datetime="2025-08-11T15:47:25-05:00">August 11, 2025 at 3:47 PM</time>				</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

							</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Can you use regular flour?<br />
If yes would it be the same amount? Thx</p>
			</div><!-- .comment-content -->

			<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-905345" data-commentid="905345" data-postid="46896" data-belowelement="div-comment-905345" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Nancy A Rini" aria-label="Reply to Nancy A Rini">Reply</a></div>		</article><!-- .comment-body -->
	<ol class="children">
	<li id="comment-905462" class="comment byuser comment-author-admin bypostauthor odd alt depth-2 staff">
		<article id="div-comment-905462" class="comment-body">
			<footer class="comment-meta">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
										<b class="fn">Kathryne Taylor</b>				</div><!-- .comment-author -->

				<div class="comment-metadata">
					<time datetime="2025-08-12T13:43:28-05:00">August 12, 2025 at 1:43 PM</time>				</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

							</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Hi Nancy, it would require a few adjustments. You could make the topping by following the method and ingredients in my <a href="https://cookieandkate.com/blueberry-scones/" rel="ugc">scones recipe</a> (skip the blueberries and bake according to this recipe&#8217;s instructions) but I preferred the almond flour version&#8217;s flavor and texture.</p>
			</div><!-- .comment-content -->

			<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-905462" data-commentid="905462" data-postid="46896" data-belowelement="div-comment-905462" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Kathryne Taylor" aria-label="Reply to Kathryne Taylor">Reply</a></div>		</article><!-- .comment-body -->
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ol><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li id="comment-905353" class="comment even thread-even depth-1 parent">
		<article id="div-comment-905353" class="comment-body">
			<footer class="comment-meta">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
										<b class="fn">Dianne Lemieux</b>				</div><!-- .comment-author -->

				<div class="comment-metadata">
					<time datetime="2025-08-11T17:48:13-05:00">August 11, 2025 at 5:48 PM</time>				</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

							</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>This was my very first cobbler and it got rave reviews! Loved that it is gluten free so that it was safe for my daughter to enjoy as well. The almond topping was soooo good. This recipe is going into my &#8220;keeper&#8221; folder. Thanks once again Kate. Actually, I never made one of your recipes that wasn&#8217;t a keeper! Look forward to the next one.</p>
<p class="tasty-recipes-ratings"><span class="tasty-recipes-rating tasty-recipes-rating-solid" data-tr-clip="100" data-rating="1"><svg class="tasty-recipes-svg" width="18" height="17"><use href="#wpt-star-full"></use></svg></span><span class="tasty-recipes-rating tasty-recipes-rating-solid" data-tr-clip="100" data-rating="2"><svg class="tasty-recipes-svg" width="18" height="17"><use href="#wpt-star-full"></use></svg></span><span class="tasty-recipes-rating tasty-recipes-rating-solid" data-tr-clip="100" data-rating="3"><svg class="tasty-recipes-svg" width="18" height="17"><use href="#wpt-star-full"></use></svg></span><span class="tasty-recipes-rating tasty-recipes-rating-solid" data-tr-clip="100" data-rating="4"><svg class="tasty-recipes-svg" width="18" height="17"><use href="#wpt-star-full"></use></svg></span><span class="tasty-recipes-rating tasty-recipes-rating-solid" data-tr-clip="100" data-rating="5"><svg class="tasty-recipes-svg" width="18" height="17"><use href="#wpt-star-full"></use></svg></span></p>
			</div><!-- .comment-content -->

			<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-905353" data-commentid="905353" data-postid="46896" data-belowelement="div-comment-905353" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Dianne Lemieux" aria-label="Reply to Dianne Lemieux">Reply</a></div>		</article><!-- .comment-body -->
	<ol class="children">
